<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 01 at 11:01AM MST  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A heavy snow shower will impact the northern portions of
northwestern Beaverhead County through 1145 AM MST...
At 1058 AM MST, Doppler radar was tracking a heavy snow shower
extending along a line extending from 16 miles north of Wisdom to 9
miles north of Gibbonsville. Movement was northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...A short period of heavy snow, with visibility less than a
half mile at times.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...The heavy snow shower will mainly affect areas north of
Highway 43, in northern Beaverhead County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If driving through this snow shower, slow down or pull over in areas
of poor visibility.</instruction>
